(669, 'Alkyn - Let Yourself Free', 'Alkyn delivers a brand new dancefloor weapon!\n\n\"The initial idea for the track was made about 3 years ago. I found a sample which almost instantly gave me an idea for a bass-line. The track came together quite naturally. Its lighthearted, bright vocal elements in conjunction with the bold character of the bass, give rise to an unexpectedly soothing yet danceable club track\".\n\n-\n\nFollow Alkyn\nhttps://myurls.co/alkyn\nhttps://www.instagram.com/alkynmusic\n\nFollow KUMO\nhttps://kumocollective.com\nhttps://www.instagram.com/kumocollective\nhttps://www.tiktok.com/@kumocollective', 819, 'https://discoveryprovider3.audius.co/v1/tracks/W6ZJpmK/stream'),
(670, 'Blush & Pala Chrome - Deep Dive ', 'For this week’s release, we’re bringing you on an intercontinental trip 🌍✨ Super hyped to welcome back Blush & Pala Chrome to the label with their brand new single ‘Deep Dive’.\n\nPlay and buy: https://bfan.link/pala-chrome-blush-deep-dive', 820, 'https://discoveryprovider3.audius.co/v1/tracks/EJw63xJ/stream'),
(671, 'Aures - No Sleep', 'Aures: \"insomnia got me here\".\n\n-\n\nPlay and buy: https://bfan.link/aures-no-sleep\n\n-\n\nFollow Aures\nhttps://linktr.ee/aures.wav\nhttps://www.instagram.com/Aures.wav\n\nFollow KUMO\nhttps://kumocollective.com\nhttps://www.instagram.com/kumocollective\nhttps://www.tiktok.com/@kumocollective', 821, 'https://discoveryprovider3.audius.co/v1/tracks/WV5azPo/stream'),
(672, 'V. Christie - Petrichor', 'V. Christie returns on KUMO with a glitchy, experimental UK Garage track laced with emotion. Drawing inspiration from the sonic worlds of Four Tet and Burial, Petrichor\'s raw spontaneity was brought to life through improvised sessions with MIDI controllers and analog synths. \n\nListen & buy: https://bfan.link/v-christie-petrichor\n\n-\n\nFollow V.Christie\nhttps://linktr.ee/v.christie\nhttps://www.instagram.com/v.christie_\nhttps://www.tiktok.com/@v.christie_\n\nFollow KUMO\nhttps://kumocollective.com\nhttps://www.instagram.com/kumocollective\nhttps://www.tiktok.com/@kumocollective', 822, 'https://discoveryprovider3.audius.co/v1/tracks/V6kK2ka/stream'),
(673, 'Kelbin - Matter (polyfawn remix)', 'Croatian-native and experimental bass producer polyfawn steps in to deliver a club-ready remix of Kelbin\'s melodic anthem \'Matter\'.\n\nPlay and buy: https://bfan.link/matter-polyfawn-remix\n\n-\n\nFollow polyfawn\nhttps://www.instagram.com/polyfawn\nhttps://x.com/polyfawn\nhttps://www.tiktok.com/@polyfawn\nhttps://linktr.ee/polyfawn\n\nFollow KUMO\nhttps://kumocollective.com\nhttps://www.instagram.com/kumocollective\nhttps://substack.com/@kumocollective', 816, 'https://discoveryprovider2.audius.co/v1/tracks/mlPwax5/stream'),
(674, 'Maynix - Automatic', 'I really wanted to combine a sunny, dancefloor-ready UK garage mood with razor-sharp sound design. I’m proud that Automatic hits like a self-driving groove, skippy UKG drums, lush chords and surgically engineered glitches all locked on cruise control -- Maynix\n\nListen & download: https://bfan.link/automatic-9\n\n-\n\nFollow Maynix\nhttps://www.instagram.com/maynix___\nhttps://www.tiktok.com/@maynix\n\nFollow KUMO\nhttps://kumocollective.substack.com\nhttps://www.instagram.com/kumocollective\nhttps://www.tiktok.com/@kumocollective', 823, 'https://discoveryprovider2.audius.co/v1/tracks/G5P8l4v/stream'),
(675, 'Aures - Pickme', 'Aurés delivers a club weapon ready to charm the heart of hardcore ravers and afterparty aficionados. Pickme is dance music in its most essential form, stripped of frills and focused only on the fundamentals. The French touch never misses!\n\nPlay and buy: https://bfan.link/pickme\n\n-\n\nFollow Aures\nhttps://linktr.ee/aures.wav\nhttps://www.instagram.com/Aures.wav\n\nFollow KUMO\nhttps://kumocollective.com\nhttps://www.instagram.com/kumocollective\nhttps://www.tiktok.com/@kumocollective', 824, 'https://discoveryprovider2.audius.co/v1/tracks/0AJgkGm/stream'),
(676, 'DANN - wanting more', 'Premiered live at the latest KUMO INVITES show in Amsterdam, \'wanting more\' marks DANN\'s debut on the label. It showcases the more emotional and musical side of the Dutch producer\'s sound — subtle, detailed, and full of feeling. Built on a unique groove and rich textures, it’s a song that pulls you inward and lets emotions surface.\n\nPlay and buy: https://bfan.link/wanting-more\n\n-\n\nFollow DANN\nhttps://www.instagram.com/soundslikedann\nhttps://www.tiktok.com/@soundslikedann\n\nFollow KUMO\nhttps://kumocollective.com\nhttps://www.instagram.com/kumocollective\nhttps://www.tiktok.com/@kumocollective', 825, 'https://discoveryprovider2.audius.co/v1/tracks/ZPpYwN7/stream'),
(677, 'not yes. - Bassline One', 'Following their fierce set at our latest KUMO INVITES event, we once again joined forces with Dutch duo not yes. to unleash Bassline One: an unapologetic banger that diabolically wobbles between dubstep and trap. A sophisticated charmer when listened to with headphones, a wild beast when played on the dancefloor.\n\nPlay and buy: https://bfan.link/bassline-one\n\n-\n\nFollow not yes.\nhttps://notyes.id\nhttps://www.instagram.com/not___yes/\n\nFollow KUMO\nhttps://kumocollective.com\nhttps://www.instagram.com/kumocollective\nhttps://www.tiktok.com/@kumocollective', 826, 'https://discoveryprovider2.audius.co/v1/tracks/WVGOlYk/stream'),
(678, 'stuckinwaveforms - Kinetic Energy', 'Drum&Bass is back on the menù!\nFrench producer stuckinwaveforms delivers a starry-eyed roller, a sample of premium liquid gold that nods to vintage sounds.\n\nListen + download: https://bfan.link/kinetic-energy\n\n-\n\nFollow stuckinwaveforms \nhttps://linktr.ee/stuckinwaveforms\nhttps://www.instagram.com/stuckinwaveforms\n\nFollow KUMO\nhttps://kumocollective.com\nhttps://www.instagram.com/kumocollective\nhttps://www.tiktok.com/@kumocollective', 827, 'https://discoveryprovider2.audius.co/v1/tracks/NQ91axp/stream');
Zonii Bio\n\n Cash Recanzone, widely recognized as Zonii, is a seasoned producer with over a decade of experience. He specializes in crafting bone-crushing bass music that will undoubtedly shake you to your core. With an impressive track record, Zonii has taken his electrifying sound on tour throughout the West Coast, captivating audiences of thousands.\nOne of his crowning achievements was the hit single \"Spaceship,\" which soared to the #1 spot on the EDM.com Trap Charts, solidifying his position as a dominant force in the music industry. Zonii is steadily ascending to the pinnacle of Los Angeles\' vibrant bass music scene, thanks to his unwavering commitment to creating some of the most original tracks and delivering unmatched DJ sets that could easily headline any major festival.\n\n\nInstagram: https://www.instagram.com/zoniiworld/\nSoundcloud: https://soundcloud.com/zoniiworld\nSpotify:https://open.spotify.com/artist/4xcptIEiB4kaNvdTrqcmwa?si=-j4TS6beQRCLOaeJT7hXzA', 1072, 'https://discoveryprovider.audius.co/v1/tracks/V0GoAZa/stream'),
(882, 'Zonii - Find The Way', 'Out Now! ', 1073, 'https://discoveryprovider3.audius.co/v1/tracks/pzjqxmY/stream'),
(883, 'Nelly Furtado - Maneater (Tony Metric Remix)', '🔥🖤 CLASSIC REBORN // CLUB WEAPON ALERT 🖤🔥\n\nMANEATER – Tony Metric Remix 🎧⚡\n\nI took this legendary classic and turned it into a full-on underground dancefloor weapon 💣\nHypnotic groove, heavy bass, driving energy and pure club vibes 🕺💃\n\nIf you’re into tech house / underground energy, this one is for you 😈🔥', 1075, 'https://discoveryprovider2.audius.co/v1/tracks/A7MmXa7/stream'),
(884, 'Britney Spears - Toxic (Tony Metric Remix)', 'YOU ASKED FOR IT!⚠️🔥\n\nPercussive grooves.\nHeavy low-end.\nHypnotic lead synths.\n\nNot just a remix —\nthis is a peak-time club weapon designed to ignite dancefloors.\n\n🚨 Support & repost if you feel the energy\n🎧 OUT NOW', 1076, 'https://discoveryprovider3.audius.co/v1/tracks/EvV2d2r/stream'),
(885, 'Tony Metric - Rawness (Extended Mix)', 'RAWNESS – a hypnotic tech house weapon built for dark rooms and sweaty crowds.\nRaw percussion, thick bass movement, trippy vocals and deep atmospheres that lock you into the groove.\n\nClose your eyes. Feel the pressure. Let it roll. 🌀', 1077, 'https://discoveryprovider2.audius.co/v1/tracks/KbElGEo/stream'),
(886, 'Gordo - Loco Loco (Tony Metric Remix)', 'The hottest track right now — flipped into a Latin Tech club weapon.\nGroovy percussion, spicy rhythms and a heavy low-end built to destroy dancefloors.\n\nThis one hits different.\nPure Latin energy. Pure club pressure. 🌶️🔥', 1078, 'https://discoveryprovider2.audius.co/v1/tracks/W6E1R9l/stream'),
(887, 'Britney Spears ft. Madonna - Me Against The Music (Tony Metric Remix)', 'This remix turns the original into a full-on tech house weapon. Heavy drums, rolling bassline and pure club pressure from start to finish.', 1079, 'https://discoveryprovider2.audius.co/v1/tracks/wV2BAvW/stream'),
(888, 'Ciara – Goodies (Tony Metric Extended Remix)', 'Flipping the 2000s R&B / crunk classic into a modern club weapon.\nClassic energy, updated groove and heavy low-end built for today’s dancefloors.\n\nPart of my 2026 sonic evolution: bringing back the golden era with a forward-thinking club sound.', 1080, 'https://discoveryprovider3.audius.co/v1/tracks/NQvgNVx/stream'),
(889, 'Lindsay Lohan - Rumors (Tony Metric Extended Dub Mix)', 'Rumors (Dub Version) is out now on Audius.\nDeeper, stripped & club-ready. 🔊\n\nLooking for the vocal version?  https://www.beatport.com/track/rumors/20746819', 1082, 'https://discoveryprovider2.audius.co/v1/tracks/zE2wkPZ/stream'),
(890, 'Sapir Amar - Oh My (Tony Metric 3AM Mix)', 'This is my  alternative \"3AM Mix\" for Oh My By Sapir Amar.', 1084, 'https://discoveryprovider.audius.co/v1/tracks/QxJBrOG/stream'),
(891, 'Nirvana - Smells Like Teen Spirit (Tony Metric Remix)', 'A Smells Like Teen Spirit flipped into an underground tech house banger', 1085, 'https://discoveryprovider.audius.co/v1/tracks/aAmXa3a/stream'),
(892, 'Sapir Amar - Oh My (Tony Metric Remix)', 'Después de mi primer tema de Afro House melódico, he vuelto este 2026 para retomar esa linea musical y que mejor que haciendo un remix del tema de \"Oh My\"', 1086, 'https://discoveryprovider.audius.co/v1/tracks/y2qmM6Y/stream'),
(893, 'Tony Metric - My Humps (Radio Edit)', 'I have a cover song \'My Humps\' turned into a Tech House banger. In this cover I gave it my personal signature, a bit more underground and dark, while maintaining the essence of the original track. Enjoy!', 1087, 'https://discoveryprovider2.audius.co/v1/tracks/WYW57v/stream'),
(894, 'Schmoop - Stutter VIP', 'long overdue, we\'re proud to officially welcome Schmoop to the Night Owl family! a fellow Texas native, and an artist that has always been close to our hearts, from the early days of Wonky Llama (his collaborative project with Jade Cicada) getting to hear the evolution of his sound over the years has been a true joy to witness. this VIP of his track Stutter flips the original on it\'s head and brings some serious energy! if you aren\'t familiar with Schmoop, it\'s time to learn up~\n\nfollow @schmoopmusic\n\nFeel Trip, Vol. 5: Eclipse is releasing one track at a time, Mondays Wednesdays and Fridays, Feb 16th - April 1st.\n\nfeaturing works from Zelgeon, Person Online, Schmoop, Mindex, Next To Blue, Innusta, Maynix, Echo Map, OSO, Vulpey, Glass Arrowhead, gHx, Blake Skowron, Vorso, COPYCATT, Seppa, Chalky, Herzeloyde, Keota, Shanic, Qynorah, Charlie W, and Hazia.\n&\nfeaturing art and visuals by tinyghost', 1088, 'https://discoveryprovider2.audius.co/v1/tracks/Q4J7wjv/stream'),
(895, 'Feel Trip, Vol. 5: Eclipse [ALBUM TEASER]', 'a sound 10 years in the making... a return to form, following in the footsteps of our very first release (Feel Trip Vol. 1) here now 10 years later, proud and honored to share 20 brand new tracks, featuring some familiar old faces alongside some brand new members joining the nest, we are incredibly proud to finally announce: Feel Trip, Vol. 5: Eclipse.\n\nthank you to all who have continued to support and believe in Night Owl. there were times it was unclear if we were to continue onward. but the path forward has been shown, and our story is yet to unfold.\n\nthe tracks will release one at a time, Mondays Wednesdays and Fridays, February 16th - April 1st.\n\nfeaturing works from Zelgeon, Person Online, Schmoop, Mindex, Next To Blue, Innusta, Maynix, Echo Map, OSO, Vulpey, Glass Arrowhead, gHx, Blake Skowron, Vorso, COPYCATT, Seppa, Chalky, Herzeloyde, Keota, Shanic, Qynorah, Charlie W, and Hazia.\n&\nfeaturing art and visuals by tinyghost + mastering by Mindex.', 1091, 'https://discoveryprovider2.audius.co/v1/tracks/xPMYRw/stream'),
